<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BOX-AYALA-TEX </SLUG>
 
PAULA AYALA HONORED, PLANS BUSY 2000 (For use by NYTimes News
Service clients) 
By JESSE SANCHEZ 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   After receiving honors for both Fighter of The Year and Fight of
the Year from ``The Ring Magazine'' Monday in Las Vegas, boxer
Paulie Ayala of Fort Worth, Texas, learned he will follow a stellar
1999 in the ring with an even busier schedule in 2000.
</P>
<P>
   ``We want him to fight four times in 2000,'' said Bob Arum,
Ayala's promoter at Top Rank Inc. ``He's one of our stars.''
</P>
<P>
   Top Rank is seeking a TVKO pay-per-view fight date for Ayala in
March to be held either in Fort Worth or in Las Vegas. As headliner
of the card, a fight between super bantamweights Danny Romero and
Nestor Garza will precede Ayala's bout, Arum said. An opponent for
Ayala has not been determined.
</P>
<P>
   Ayala's pay-per-view bout will preface appearances on a national
cable network, Arum added.
</P>
<P>
   ``We are working on getting Paulie on Showtime or HBO,'' Arum
said. ``We want to get him on one of those at least two times in
2000.''
</P>
<P>
   Ayala fought three times last year, but said he is willing to
fight more often.
</P>
<P>
   ``I like to stay busy,'' Ayala, 29, said. ``I'm used to fighting
six times a year anyway.''
</P>
<P>
   Ayala (29-1, 12 knockouts) defeated then-undefeated champion
Johnny Tapia (46-1-2, 25 knockouts) for the World Boxing
Association's bantamweight title on June 23 for Fight of the Year.
He followed the victory with a unanimous decision against the WBA's
No. 1-rated contender, Saohin Srithai Condo, in Fort Worth on Oct.
23 in his first title defense.
</P>
<P>
   As ``The Ring Magazine'' Fighter of The Year, Ayala joins a list
of former and current champions that includes Muhammad Ali, Julio
Cesar Chavez, Evander Holyfield and Fort Worth's Donald Curry, who
shared the honor with Marvin Hagler in 1985. Floyd Mayweather Jr.
won the award in 1998.
</P>
<P>
   ``Just being nominated was satisfying enough, but this is
overwhelming,'' Ayala said. ``When he presented me with the
``Ring'' belt I thought about the famous fighters who have won
before me. It's hard to believe.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's been a good year. I had a beautiful daughter, and it just
kept on getting better and better in boxing. I just needed the
opportunity. Once I got it, I capitalized on it.'' nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-12-07-99 0141EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
