<HEADER>
A1435 &Cx1f; ttx-z
r s BC-FBN-DEION-TEX     12-07 0305
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-DEION-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
DEION MAY PLAY RECEIVER, BUT GAILEY WON'T REVEAL PLANS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By RAY BUCK 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   IRVING, Texas _ The ``possibility'' of Deion Sanders being
integrated into the Dallas Cowboys' offense, even as early as this
week against Philadelphia, had coach Chan Gailey:
</P>
<P>
   1) being evasive.
</P>
<P>
   2) being laconic.
</P>
<P>
   3) holding steadfast that even if his bare feet were held to an
open flame, he would not divulge the secret behind talks to give
Sanders some snaps at wide receiver now that the offense has scored
only four touchdowns in the past 18 quarters.
</P>
<P>
   Deion? Offense?
</P>
<P>
   ``It's not out of the realm of possibility,'' said Gailey,
backpeddling nicely.
</P>
<P>
   The mood around Valley Ranch on Monday ranged between vague and
cloaked in secrecy regarding whether Sanders can infuse a
much-needed spark to a sagging Cowboys passing game. The subject
was raised by owner Jerry Jones and Sanders himself Sunday night.
</P>
<P>
   Has Deion approached Gailey to ask to be put on offense for as
many as 10-12 plays per game?
</P>
<P>
   ``Has he dropped hints? Yes,'' said Gailey, rewording the
question and providing the answer.
</P>
<P>
   Are they subtle?
</P>
<P>
   ``Not real subtle,'' Gailey replied.
</P>
<P>
   Sanders had 36 receptions for 475 yards for the Cowboys in 1996.
Last season, he had seven receptions for 100 yards. His last catch
came 13 months ago this week in a game against the New York Giants.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're talking a lot about this now,'' Gailey said a bit
impatiently. ``We've said it's a possibility (that Sanders will
move to receiver).''
</P>
<P>
   Would Gailey prefer to drop him into the lineup against an
unsuspecting opponent rather than advertise the possibility of it
happening?
</P>
<P>
   Gailey nodded.
</P>
<P>
   ``That's ``if'' we're going to use him on offense,'' he added.
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-12-07-99 0144EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
