<HEADLINE>
USC RECEIVERS COACH WILSON MIGHT LEAVE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ The next USC assistant to depart the staff could
be wide receivers coach Mike Wilson, who might join his brother in
private business. A decision could be made as soon as this week.
</P>
<P>
   The other coach who is most often the focus of speculation,
offensive coordinator Hue Jackson, is not believed to be in
jeopardy of losing his job, according to several sources.
</P>
<P>
   USC coach Paul Hackett said he would make final decisions
regarding his staff by mid-December, but all of USC's defensive
coaches have been assured they will return.
</P>
<P>
   As reported Monday, USC officially named tight ends coach Steve
Morton as the offensive line coach, replacing Steve Greatwood, who
was fired last week.
</P>
<P>
   This leaves a vacancy at tight ends. A longshot candidate might
be former USC assistant and Los Angeles Rams lineman Doug Smith,
who met briefly with Hackett last Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   Back to Oregon?: Greatwood might be returning to his alma mater,
Oregon, although a defined role has not been established.
</P>
<P>
   ``There's a possibility. The right circumstances have to happen
there,'' Greatwood said.
</P>
<P>
   The La Crescenta resident is in no hurry to find a job, because
he still has 20 months remaining on his USC contract.
</P>
<P>
   Turner out: Men's basketball forward Jarvis Turner will miss
four to six weeks while recovering from a stress fracture in his
left foot.
</P>
<P>
   ``Losing Jarvis Turner is a serious blow to the team,'' USC
coach Henry Bibby said. ``His loss limits our versatility on the
court and we will also miss his senior leadership.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
