programs assess how certain compounds react with one another. The
result: New drugs can be developed in half the time. By Ronald
Rosenberg. PHOTO
</P>
<P>
   ONBUSINESS-COLUMN (Undated) _ Wall Street street typically
ignores what goes on in Washington. But when it comes to drug
stocks, Wall Street is paying close attention to what the
politicains have to say. By Steven Syre and Charles Stein.
</P>
