   &UR; ENTERTAINMENT (Available by 2 p.m., Thu., Dec. 9) &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   HERE COMES THE JUDGE: You can almost hear the sound of judicial
robes ripping and courtroom doors slamming as real-life jurists
around the country race for Hollywood. Court television shows are
all the rage.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: VIDEO REVIEWS: Director Renny Harlin brings his usual
hyper-drive direction to the bloody action in ``Deep Blue Sea.''
Also reviews of ``Inspector Gadget'' and ``Trippin.''
</P>
<P>
   WITH: CD REVIEWS: ``S&AMP;M,'' Metallica's 2-CD stocking stuffer of
a concept album, is a ``with strings'' adaptation of the Metallica
songbook that exploits the band's overt Wagnerian tendencies to
maximum effect. What's surprising is that it actually makes perfect
sense. Also reviews of the latest from Faith Hill and Enrique
Iglesias.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: STAR FILE: Pop superstar Billy Joel is on the road singing
all his old hits. Enjoy 'em while you can _ Joel says it's probably
the last time.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FOCUS (Available by 2 p.m., Fri., Dec. 10) &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   A HOME IN MEXICO, A JOB IN AMERICA: Illegal immigrants are both
a resource and an embarrassment for two countries. They keep
America supplied with cheap labor but highlight the U.S.
government's inability to control its borders. They send Mexico a
steady stream of dollars but serve as a constant reminder of the
government's failure to provide a decent living to millions.
</P>
