 AM-ADD-NYT-BUDGET  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Add N.Y. Times News Service budget for papers of Wednesday, Dec.
8.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; DINING &LR;
</P>
<P>
   NAPLES-RESTAURANTS (Naples, Italy) _ For decades on end, Naples
was the city Italy forgot and everyone else avoided. Poor. Dirty.
Hopelessly corrupt. But all that started to change in 1994, when
the G-7 meeting of world leaders inspired a cleanup effort here.
Mayor Antonio Bassolino promised that the self-improvement campaign
would continue after the big shots had left town. And he kept his
word. By R.W. Apple Jr.
</P>
<P>
   With sidebars: NAPLES-RECIPES and NAPLES-WINES.
</P>
<P>
   RESTAURANT-COMPLAINTS (New York) _ As anyone knows who's pressed
the redial button 50 times to make a reservation, the restaurant
boom has made the complaining issue more timely than ever. What is
the best way of getting results when you're not happy in a
restaurant _ short of phoning in a pepperoni pie? By Alex Wichtel.
</P>
<P>
   CHRISTMAS-COOKIES (Undated) _ High-yield, low-effort Christmas
cookies: a trayful in four batches. By Marian Burros. With recipes
</P>
<P>
   SALADS-CHEFS (Undated) _ Why salads taste so much better when
chefs toss them: It's all in the dressing. By Elaine Louie.
</P>
<P>
   CHINESE-BOOK-REVIEW (Undated) _ Melissa Clark reviews Eileen
Yin-Fei Lo's new Chinese cookbook. With one recipe.
</P>
<P>
   TEA-ONLINE (Undated) _ Where to go for tea online. By Shelly
Belzer.
</P>
<P>
   MASTER-CHEF (New York) _ The column: Make-ahead risotto.
</P>
<P>
   SIMPLE-COOKING (Undated) _ The column: Fish with leeks _
papillote without parchment. By Mark Bittman. With one recipe.
</P>
<P>
   WINETALK (Undated) _ The weekly wine column: Building a wine
cellar, part 2: what to invest in. By Frank J. Prial.
</P>
<P>
   TASTINGS (Undated) _ The column: Zinfandels. By Erik Asimov.
</P>
