<P>
   FEDERAL-CASELOAD (Boston) _ With criminal cases clogging dockets
in border states like Arizona and California, federal judges have
turned to Massachusetts -- and cutting-edge technolgy -- to reduce
caseloads. Judges in Boston, which has a comparatively light
caseload, are handling pretrial motions in civil cases via video
hookups with courts out west. By Shelley Murphy. 1000 words. PHOTO
</P>
