<P>
   COKE-MAIN _ ATLANTA _ Following developments at Coca-Cola in th
wake of Douglas Ivester's announcement that he will leave the
company next spring. The company's stock continues to fall after
analysts downgraded their ratings on it. ``We believe Ivester's
decision to retire is a significant loss,'' said Andrew Conway, an
analyst at Morgan Stanley Dean Witter &AMP; Co., in a report. (Unger,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   w/COKE-CEOS _ ATLANTA _ Ivester joins a long list of short-timer
ceos. Turnover at the top is high: more than half of the ceos at
the nation's fortune 500 firms have left this decade. Compared to
their predecessors, today's ceo is a short-timer. (They're staying
less than five years vs. more than 10 years in the past). They're
feeling the pinch of investor-minded boards. Many are still young
(having gotten their top jobs in their early 40s) and wealthy and
they want to strike out on their own. (Joyner, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   COKE-SON _A look at Coca-Cola's new chairman-designate, Douglas
Daft, through the eyes of his son, a student at Williams College in
Massachusetts. (Kempner, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   HDEPOT-ANALYSTS _ ATLANTA _ Home Depot begins its annual two-day
analyst conference today at company headquarters. Likely topics
include the company's Internet plans, updates on Villager's
Hardware and new Expos, and continued cost-cutting efforts. (Bond,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 10.
</P>
<P>
   MONEYTALK _ Personal finance advice. This week: The year's end
always brings an increase in donations to charity. In part, that's
because more charities ask for money right about now, and
charitable gifts are deductible on income taxes. (Ezell, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   POLIO _ Ted Turner and Bill Gates are help the CDC and other
groups' efforts to eradicate polio in the year 2000. The pair said
they will give major money - $78 million, $28m from Ted and $50m
from Bill - to the fight. (McKenna, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
