   AUTO RACING
</P>
<P>
   CAR-GORDON _ Jeff Gordon dumps crew chief Brian Whitesell and
hires crew chief of Petty team. (Carvell, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   BASKETBALL/COLLEGES
</P>
<P>
   BKC-MARKPRICE _ ATLANTA _ Mark Price played in plenty of Georgia
Tech-Georgia games. Now he will coach in one. The former Tech and
NBA standout is in his first year as an assistant coach with the
Yellow Jackets. Can he help his old coach, Bobby Cremins, get Tech
back to its past glory? Tech and Georgia play their annual game
Wednesday, in Athens. (Clemons), Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 20.
</P>
<P>
   BASKETBALL/PROS
</P>
<P>
   BKN-ODOM _ Through the first month of the season, Lamar Odom of
the Los Angeles Clippers has been the most impressive rookie in the
NBA. Odom leads his team in scoring and will lead the Clippers into
tonight's game against the Hawks. And all of this is coming from
someone who had second thoughts about entering the NBA draft last
season. After only one season at Rhode Island, Odom declared for
the draft, and then decided that he wanted to stay at Rhode Island.
he eventually remained in the draft, and he's now an early favorite
for rookie of the year. (Bunn, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 22.
</P>
<P>
   BASEBALL
</P>
<P>
   BBN-BRAVES-FREEAGENTS _ ATLANTA _ The Atlanta Braves have until
midnight to offer salary arbitration to leadoff hitter Gerald
Williams and five other free agents. By offering salary
arbitration, the Braves will receive a draft pick if Williams signs
with another team. But it is likely that Williams will re-sign with
the Braves. (Stinson, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 12.
</P>
