<SLUG> BC-FBC-WARRICK-HEISMAN-NYTR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
A LETDOWN FOR FLORIDA STATE'S WARRICK 
</HEADLINE>
   (bl)  
 By KEVIN RECORD   
 NYT Regional Newspapers   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   TALLAHASSEE, Fla. _ Peter Warrick is the best football player on
the No. 1-ranked college team in the nation, but a late-September
discount shopping spree cost him any chance of being recognized as
one of the best players in the country.
</P>
<P>
   Warrick, who was the leading contender for the Heisman Trophy
heading into October, was not among the five finalists invited to
Saturday night's trophy presentation at the Downtown Athletic Club
in New York.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm very hurt,'' said Warrick, who highlighted FSU's first
practice since the end of the regular season with a 50-yard TD
reception from quarterback Chris Weinke. ``I know I made a mistake.
But what does something that happened off the field have to do with
what you do every Saturday?''
</P>
<P>
   Warrick was ultimately charged with misdemeanor theft for
purchasing, along with teammate Laveranues Coles, more than $400
worth of clothing for roughly $20 at a local department store.
</P>
<P>
   Consequently, Warrick missed FSU's games with Miami and Wake
Forest, but finished the season with 71 receptions for 934 yards.
In the regular-season finale at Florida, a 30-23 FSU victory,
Warrick had nine receptions for 90 yards and rushed for the
Seminoles first touchdown, taking the snap from center out of the
shotgun formation.
</P>
<P>
   ``Every Saturday I came to play,'' Warrick said. ``I thought the
award was supposed to go to the guy who did the most to help his
team won.
</P>
<P>
   ``I feel like I did a lot for this team.''
</P>
<P>
   Warrick will get one more chance to prove his worth on Jan. 4,
when the Seminoles (11-0) take on second-ranked Virginia Tech
(11-0) in the Sugar Bowl.
</P>
<P>
   ``I've been watching a lot of film on Florida State and I've
seen the moves that Warrick put on defenders this season,''
Virginia Tech Coach Frank Beamer said after the bowl lineup was
officially announced Sunday. ``It just about ruined my day. I don't
know how you cover him.''
</P>
<P>
   (Kevin Record is a sports writer for the New York Times Regional
Newspapers.)
</P>
</TEXT>
