   CHECHNYA-RUSSIA (Primykaniye, Russia) _ Just last week, it was
the Islamic rebels who held this bucolic settlement, a mere two and
half miles from the outskirts of Grozny. But as Russian troops
rushed to encircle the Chechen capital, the outnumbered rebels were
routed in a furious 10-hour firefight against Russian helicopters,
artillery, and tanks. Russian commanders boast about their use of
maneuver and deception. But the most enduring impression from a
three-day visit to Chechnya is of massive firepower. By Michael R.
Gordon.
