   .
</P>
<P>
   FREEWAY-TRAFFIC (Los Angeles) -- California Assemblyman Wally
Knox urged Caltrans on Tuesday to fast-track improvements at the
101-405 interchange under a new law that allows partial constuction
before full design. The law, which Knox sponsored, allows six
projects this year to be started without being fully designed.
Caltrans has already fast-tracked the 101-405 project's
environmental review, and is supposed to pick the projects for the
AB 405 pilot program by the end of the year. By Steve Carney. (Will
move on the ``n'' California news wire.)
</P>
<P>
   UNI-CITYWALK (Los Angeles) -- Universal CityWalk is on track to
complete its ambitious expansion in April, adding 34 new tenants as
the flashy entertainment district seeks to bolster its status as a
key destination for tourists and locals.By Dave McNary. (Will move
on the ``f'' financial news wire.)
</P>
<P>
   AMGEN-CEO (Los Angeles) -- Amgen Inc.'s Gordon Binder is
resigning as chief executive officer on May 11, following the
company's annual stockholders meeting, and as board chairman and a
director by Dec. 31, 2000. Kevin W. Sharer, president and chief
operating officer of the Thousand Oaks-based biotechnology company
since 1992, will succeed Binder. By Jason Z. Cohen.(Will move on
the ``f'' financial news wire.)
</P>
