<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL; 
Y2KFLIGHTS (Phoenix) - As midnight nears in Arizona on New Year's,
FAA chief Jane Garvey will fly over the Four Corners region in
virtually empty skies.
</P>
<P>
   Her flight, aimed at reassuring travelers that Y2K glitches
won't cause planes to fall out of the sky, will have little
commercial air traffic to contend with as airlines scale back their
flight schedules. Still, flights will be scarce as the new
millennium approaches. By PETER CORBETT. Story will move in the
``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
DEBATE-EDIT (Phoenix) - If Monday evening's debate among all six
Republican presidential aspirants proved anything, it was this:
Given a chance to grill each other, none of these fellows ever met
a softball question served gently over the plate that he didn't
like. Story moved in the ``K'' category. &QL; 
