2 and a half miles from the outskirts of Grozny. But as Russian
troops rushed to encircle the Chechen capital, the outnumbered
rebels were routed in a furious 10-hour firefight against Russian
helicopters, artillery, and tanks. Russian commanders boast about
their use of maneuver and deception, but the most enduring
impression from a three-day visit to Chechnya is of massive
