<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR WEDNESDAY, DECEMBER 8
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Wednesday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-MEXICO-GRAVES-NYT (moved on Friday, Dec. 3)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Friday, Dec. 3,
about the search by Mexican and American law enforcement agencies
for bodies believed to be buried at a drug trafficker's farm near
Ciudad Juarez referred incorrectly to the arrival of the Mexican
attorney general, Jorge Madrazo, and the director of the Federal
Bureau of Investigation, Louis Freeh, at the farm. According to a
letter from the F.B.I.'s office of public and congressional
affairs, they arrived by car, not in the two helicopters that
landed at the farm at the same time.
</P>
</TEXT>
