LOAMY-ART -- William Dilworth, curator of Walter de Maria's ``New
York Room,'' a sculpture made up of 250 cubic yards of earth piled
22 inches deep. Some 10,000 people visit the piece annually. One
can't walk on it - a glass barrier contains the earth and keeps
people out - but a loamy smell definitely permeates the space. (Don
Hogan Charles/The New York Times)
</P>
