<P>
   (NYT7) NEW YORK -- Dec. 7, 1999 -- SALADS-CHEFS-1 -- Franklin
Becker of Local pours his sherry-shallot vinaigrette. Enter the
stealth salad dressing, invisible to the eye but evident to the
tongue. It is the reason that many salads in restaurants these days
have a delicious yet elusive quality that may puzzle diners trying
to replicate them at home. (Norman Y. Lono/The New York Times) LITE
