 &UR; INCUBATOR  &LR; _ Venture Frogs is not your typical venture or angel
capital firm. To stay close to their tadpole clients, co-founders
Tony Hsieh, 25, and Alfred Lin, 26, located their business
incubator in the same building where they live. They are even
putting in a restaurant so their adopted offspring can concentrate
on building their products and market share rather than foraging
for food. ``The concept is to get everyone to work all the time and
never leave the building,'' said Hsieh, only half-jokingly. Venture
Frogs is renovating 10,000 square feet of space in the Marquee
Historical Building at 1000 Van Ness Ave. in San Francisco to
create a nursery for up to 15 Internet startups. By Peter Sinton
