A2225 &Cx1f; ttj-z
u s BC-FBC-UH-OSBORNE-HNS &LR;      12-07 0351
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBC-UH-OSBORNE-HNS </SLUG>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By JERRY WIZIG  
 c. 1999, Houston Chronicle  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Former Nebraska football coach Tom Osborne will not be the
University of Houston's next coach.
</P>
<P>
   A radio station in Nebraska reported that Osborne was headed to
UH and would receive a financial package worth $1 million a year,
but Cougars athletic director Chet Gladchuk shot down the report
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   ``Tom Osborne is not going to be the next football coach at this
university and never was going to be the next football coach,''
Gladchuk said. ``There is no truth to that report, period.''
</P>
<P>
   Osborne, 62, was 255-49-3 in 25 seasons with Nebraska and won
national championships in 1994, 1995 and 1997. Osborne remains
active at Nebraska with teaching, alumni affairs and fund-raising.
He recently appraised the UH program for Gladchuk during a visit to
Houston.
</P>
<P>
   ``I wanted to have the insight and input of the coach who
created the benchmark for excellence in our profession,'' Gladchuk
said of Osborne's role. ``I wanted to be able to rely on his
appraisal so that I could share that with interested candidates for
this position at the proper time.''
</P>
<P>
   Under state hiring policies, Friday is the earliest the Cougars
can announce a successor to Kim Helton, their coach for the past
seven seasons who was dismissed Nov. 21 with two years remaining on
his contract.
</P>
<P>
   ``This is a very careful and calculated process, and I have
guaranteed the utmost confidence to all who have showed any
interest in the position,'' Gladchuk said. ``I am responsible to
all of them to live up to that commitment of privacy. I have
promised whoever has showed interest that to the utmost of my
ability, I will live up to that. I won't jeopardize any chance of
this university to hire the best possible coach, and I will not
address any reports or rumors of candidates.
</P>
<P>
   ``So the best thing I can say is that I promise we will have a
new coach by the season opener and everyone should relax and go
Christmas shopping. We will complete our process as soon as
possible.''
</P>
</TEXT>
